tossup_question: 1) MATH  Consider the function y = sin (1/x). Which of the following statements holds true for this function?
tossup_MCQoptions:
W) The function has no limit as x approaches zero from either side
X) The function has a left-handed limit as x approaches zero 
Y) The function has a right-handed limit as x approaches zero
Z) The function has a limit as x approaches zero as both the right- and left-handed limits exist
tossup_answer: ANSWER: W) The function has no limit as x approaches zero from either side
